	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In my experience, an NTSC TV still in operation may hide up to 8 pixels on each side, 16 on top, and 11 on bottom. Early games, such as <em>Super Mario Bros.</em> and <em>The Legend of Zelda</em>, were designed for 1970s TVs that could hide up to 16 on each side and 24 on top and bottom. For more information, see <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Overscan" class="postlink">Overscan</a>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


